            <scopecontent>
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                                 <p>Bishop Hill Colony, founded in 1846, was a fairly self-contained Swedish communitarian society in Henry County Illinois, engaging in agriculture, linen weaving, and the production of woolen goods.</p>
                                 <p>The correspondence, copied from originals in the Illinois State Historical Library, is published in Harry E. Pratt, &quot;The Murder of Eric Janson, Leader of the Bishop Hill Colony,&quot; <emph render="italic">Journal of the Illinois State Historical Society</emph>, 45 (Spring 1952), 55-69.</p>
                        </scopecontent>
            


